The following assumptions were used to estimate the fault tolerant time interval:
* The sensor interface essentially transmits data from the element host controller to the sensor and vice versa.
* It is assumed that communication errors and errors in internal processing can be easily recognized and reported to the host controller.

This leads to an assumed fault tolerant time interval (FTTI) of 50 ms.

children.description:
The PLL locks an internal RC oscillator to an 500kHz reference clock connected to the device pin CLKREF. It is an Integer-N PLL with fixed divider ratio of 36:1.
The oscillator clock is divided by an asynchronous 2:1 divider followed by an 5Bit programmable frequency divider. The ratio is of the programmable frequency divider is set to a fixed value of 18:1 in the cell DIV36.
children.name: PLL

children.description:
All characteristics are taken from simulation in '''HERNE 0.6.1''' (15.08.2016). Typical parameter values correspond to VSUP = 1.8V, Temperature = 25°C, Corner = tt. 
Max and min values correspond to edge values taken from simulation for complete supply and temperature range and all corners. 
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

'''Notes:'''
 
1. Initial accuracy describes the deviation from the nominal frequency within the entire range of supply
voltages, junction temperatures and all corners at '''nominal TRIM code'''.

2. Adjusted accuracy describes the deviation from the nominal frequency within the entire range of supply
voltages, junction temperatures and all corners at '''best TRIM code'''.

3. Equivalent Temperature Coefficient ('''TCF''') is calculated for every corner parameter set and supply voltage by box method:
$$TCF=\frac{MAX(F_{OUT})-MIN(F_{OUT})}{(T_{MAX}-T_{MIN})*F_{OUT}(25°C)}*10^{6}$$.
Temperature coefficient calculated by box-method is always positive.

4. Power Supply Rejection Ratio is calculated for every corner parameter set and temperature:
$$PSRR=20*lg|\frac{(F_{OUT}(1.93V)/F_{OUT}(1.67V))-1}{(1.93V/1.67V)-1}|$$

5. Threshold for duty cycle measurement is VSUP/2.

6. Nominal trimming range describes the range, in which the frequency can be trimmed at nominal conditions.

7. Trimming range describes the range, in which the frequency can be trimmed within the entire range of supply voltages, junction temperatures and all corners.

8. LSB is calculated in the middle range TRIM 82-->83

content: This safety mechanism addresses faults within the DSI3 communication.

content:
The IC shall provide a mechanism to generate and assess redundant data in communication frames. This mechanism shall on the one hand provide redundant transmit data to the slaves (payload CRC for read data in frames) and on the other hand validate the received redundant data (payload CRC for  write data in frames). 
This mechanism shall ensure data integrity on the DSI3 bus line. In case of inconsistencies the received frame shall be marked as faulty.

content: Error Detection and Correction for Memories/Registers
children.name: Row 1

content: This safety mechanism addresses faults in memories and registers on data word level. It can detect and - if required and possible - correct corrupted content in memory cells and registers.
children.name: Row 2

content: The content of SRAM, OTP and registers of communication path is extended by redundant information, which allows to validate the memory cell or register content on every read access. The added redundant information is calculated in such a way, that it allows to correct single bit failures and to detect double bit failures per data word (SECDED). This corresponds to a minimum Hamming distance of 4.

The redundant data of the address protection shall be evaluated after every read access.
